FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774458667
OL,3,CParties have not stood shoulder to
OL,4,Cshoulder to support police ` Chief
OL,5,CConstable
OL,7,FDUP leader Gavin Robinson pushed back
OL,8,Fon the suggestion that there was a
OL,9,F"collective" political problem,
OL,10,Fpointing out that support for policing
OL,11,Ffrom most parties was "unconscious".
OL,13,FMr Boutcher was asked about police
OL,14,Frecruitment when he gave evidence to
OL,15,Fthe Northern Ireland Affairs Committee.
OL,17,FFigures released by the PSNI following
OL,18,Ftheir latest recruitment drive showed
OL,19,Fthat the percentage of new Catholic
OL,20,Fapplicants to join the force was at
OL,21,Fits lowest in more than a decade.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@LO]sD@WOUsD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774458667
OL,3,CParties have not stood shoulder to
OL,4,Cshoulder to support police ` Chief
OL,5,CConstable
OL,7,FPolice said more than 4,000 people had
OL,8,Fapplied for their latest student
OL,9,Fofficer recruitment campaign, with
OL,10,F65.6% from a Protestant background,
OL,11,F26.7% from a Catholic background and
OL,12,F7.7% undetermined.
OL,14,FMr Boutcher said: "All political
OL,15,Fparties need to help us far more than
OL,16,Fthey have."
OL,26,@vD@SOUxD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774458667
OL,3,CParties have not stood shoulder to
OL,4,Cshoulder to support police ` Chief
OL,5,CConstable
OL,7,FHe pointed out that the Patten Report,
OL,8,Fwhich led to the creation of the PSNI
OL,9,Fin 2001, said all community, religious
OL,10,Fand political leaders should support
OL,11,Fthe force and stop any discouragement
OL,12,Fof people joining.
OL,14,FMr Boutcher said: "They should
OL,15,Factively encourage young people to
OL,16,Fjoin the PSNI, none of that's
OL,17,Fhappened."
OL,26,@vD@SOUyD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774458667
OL,3,CParties have not stood shoulder to
OL,4,Cshoulder to support police ` Chief
OL,5,CConstable
OL,7,FMr Robinson responded: "That's not
OL,8,Fright... it is right in part, but I am
OL,9,Fnot going to take any criticism of our
OL,10,Fsupport for policing because you know
OL,11,Fwhere we stand."
OL,13,FThe Chief Constable said: "It has not
OL,14,Fhappened as collectively as it needs
OL,15,Fto happen, we need to be shoulder to
OL,16,Fshoulder on that."
OL,18,FMr Boutcher said the force also needed
OL,19,Fto get better at telling its own story
OL,20,Fto encourage people to join.
OL,26,@oD@XOUsD@PO]uD@[OUxD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774458667
OL,3,CParties have not stood shoulder to
OL,4,Cshoulder to support police ` Chief
OL,5,CConstable
OL,7,FHe added: "Not all political parties
OL,8,Fhave come in to support policing in
OL,9,Fthe way that I think the Patten
OL,10,FCommission envisaged... in a way that
OL,11,Fis literally shoulder to shoulder."
OL,13,FThe Chief Constable said he had had a
OL,14,Fconversation with Peadar Heffron, a
OL,15,Fformer officer whose leg was amputated
OL,16,Ffollowing a dissident republican bomb
OL,17,Fattack on his car in 2010 in Co Antrim.
OL,26,@oD@KOUsD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774458667
OL,3,CParties have not stood shoulder to
OL,4,Cshoulder to support police ` Chief
OL,5,CConstable
OL,7,FHe said: "Paedar told me that when he
OL,8,Ftold his GAA teammates he was going to
OL,9,Fjoin the police, a number of them
OL,10,Fdidn't speak to him.
OL,12,F"He said to me 'I am not sure it would
OL,13,Fhave changed today'.
OL,15,F"That is not the progress that any of
OL,16,Fus want."
OL,18,F"Many people who join the PSNI from a
OL,19,Fnationalist background fear that some
OL,20,Fof the community won't speak to them
OL,21,Fagain.
OL,26,@oD@JOUtD@AOUwD@AOUxD@IO]zD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774458667
OL,3,CParties have not stood shoulder to
OL,4,Cshoulder to support police ` Chief
OL,5,CConstable
OL,7,F"I find that hard to understand as a
OL,8,Fpolice officer, how that can be, but
OL,9,Fit is the case."
OL,11,FMr Boutcher also addressed calls for a
OL,12,Freturn to a 50-50 recruitment policy,
OL,13,Fto boost the number of officers from a
OL,14,Fnationalist background in the force.
OL,16,FHe said: "I always say nothing is off
OL,17,Fthe table because I will consider
OL,18,Fanything.
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@PO]xD@JOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,446,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1774458667
OL,3,CParties have not stood shoulder to
OL,4,Cshoulder to support police ` Chief
OL,5,CConstable
OL,7,F"But I think if we did what Chris
OL,8,FPatten had promoted that we should do
OL,9,Fin his report in 1999, I would hope we
OL,10,Fwould see the number of applicants
OL,11,Ffrom the Catholic/nationalist
OL,12,Fcommunity increase to 35-40%,
OL,13,Fproportionally to the representation
OL,14,Fthey have in society.
OL,16,F"That is what we need to do.
OL,18,F"I think 50-50 feels to me a lazy way
OL,19,Fto do it. We need to do the work to
OL,20,Fmake sure we get the support from
OL,21,Fsociety."
OL,26,@oD@AOUxD@AOUzD@AOU}D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/14
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
